sec.p:
The progression criteria to judge the feasibility of progressing to a full trial were that following the six-month follow-up data collection [36]:
≥50% of eligible participants recruited into the feasibility study;
≥70% of the participants in the intervention arm completed nine to twelve sessions in the exercise programme.
≥70% of participants had data collected on main outcomes at six-month follow-up;
< 10% of serious adverse events deemed due to the intervention.
